quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  22,31,"Be upright Ë¹in devotionËº to God, associating none with Him Ë¹in worshipËº. For whoever associates Ë¹othersËº with God is like someone who has fallen from the sky and is either snatched away by birds or swept by the wind to a remote place"
  22,32,"That is so. And whoever honours the symbols of God, it is certainly out of the piety of the heart"
  22,33,"You may benefit from sacrificial animals for an appointed term,Â then their place of sacrifice is at the Ancient House"
  22,34,"For every community We appointed a rite of sacrifice so that they may pronounce the Name of God over the sacrificial animals He has provided for them. For your God is only One God, so submit yourselves to Him Ë¹aloneËº. And give good news Ë¹O ProphetËº to the humble"
  22,35,"those whose hearts tremble at the remembrance of God, who patiently endure whatever may befall them, and who establish prayer and donate from what We have provided for them"
  22,36,"We have made sacrificial camels Ë¹and cattleËº among the symbols of God, in which there is Ë¹muchËº good for you. So pronounce the Name of God over them when they are lined up Ë¹for sacrificeËº. Once they have fallen Ë¹lifelessËº on their sides, you may eat from their meat, and feed the needyâ€”those who do not beg, and those who do. In this way We have subjected these Ë¹animalsËº to you so that you may be grateful"
  22,37,"Neither their meat nor blood reaches God. Rather, it is your piety that reaches Him. This is how He has subjected them to you so that you may proclaim the greatness of God for what He has guided you to, and give good news to the good-doers"
  22,38,"Indeed, God defends those who believe. Surely God does not like whoever is deceitful, ungrateful"
